	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1" facs="EHRI-ET-YV3540317_01.jpg"/>
			<p><placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/598998/ignalina.html">Ignalina</placeName> (<placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/864522/svencionys.html">Švenčionys district</placeName>). A <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">work camp</term> of the <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-433">organization Dat</orgName> (or <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-433">Todt</orgName>) was located there from the month of <date
					when="1942-04">April 1942</date> until <date when="1943-03-30">March 30, 1943</date>. The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">work</term> was comprised of chopping [wood in the]
				forest near <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/598998/ignalina.html">Ignalina</placeName> and also [working] on the railway line.
				In the year <date when="1942">1942</date>, around 150 people from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html"
					>Vilna</placeName> as well as <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/621713/smarhon.html">Smarhoń</placeName> (<placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/621713/smarhon.html">Smorgon</placeName>) and <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/630515/ashmyany.html">Ashmyana</placeName> (<placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/630515/ashmyany.html">Oshmene</placeName>) worked there. At the end of <date when="1942">1942</date>,
				a great number became <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">sick</term> with <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-493" type="subject">typhus</term>, they succeeded in <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject">transporting</term> the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-493" type="subject">sick</term> to <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/864522/svencionys.html">Švenčionys</placeName> to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term> and they never returned. In their stead
				workers were sent from the shtetls of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/620191/vidzy.html">Vidzy</placeName>, <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/628869/druysk.html">Druysk</placeName>, <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/564792/dubina.html"
					>Dubina</placeName>.</p>
			<p>The <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> did not treat the Jewish <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1057" type="subject">workers</term> badly, most of all the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-477" type="subject">camp director</term>, a lieutenant form <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/3099434/gdansk.html">Danzig</placeName> (I have forgotten his name), distinguished himself. He would
				allow the Jews to go begging in the villages and to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject"
					>work</term> for Christians three to four days per month, but no one should say that he had allowed them to do so.</p>
			<p>At the end of <date when="1943-03">March 1943</date>, all the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1057"
					type="subject">workers</term> had to be sent to the <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-1103"
					type="ghetto">ghetto in Švenčionys</placeName>. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1057"
					type="subject">workers</term> cried when they parted with the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term>. The
				lieutenant and another two of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-477" type="subject">watchmen</term>
				cried. Of all the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1057" type="subject">workers</term> only two remain
				alive, one from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/620191/vidzy.html">Vidzy</placeName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_tvaretsky_leib"
					>Leib Tvaretsky</persName>, and a young <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject"
					>woman</term> from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/628869/druysk.html">Dryusk</placeName>, <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_feygin_sheyne">Sheyne Feygin</persName>. They must be in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2921044/federal-republic-of-germany.html">Germany</placeName>,</p>
			<p>In the year <date when="1945">1945</date>, I found in the home of a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-763"
					type="subject">Christian</term> in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/598998/ignalina.html">Ignalina</placeName> a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-701" type="subject">photograph</term> of a group of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1057" type="subject">workers</term> from the <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-1529" type="camp">Ignalina camp</placeName>. I gave the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-701" type="subject">photo</term> to the Historical <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-705" type="subject">Museum</term> in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/3093133/lodz.html">Lodz</placeName>, to Mr. <persName ref="#ehri_et_kaczerginski_sherke">Sh.
					Kaczerginski</persName>.</p>
			<p><placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2867714/munich.html">Munich</placeName>, <date when="1946-07-07">7/7/46</date>
				<persName ref="#ehri_et_korb_yerachmiel">Yerachmiel Korb</persName> from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/598998/ignalina.html"
					>Ignalina</placeName>, <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/864522/svencionys.html">Švenčionys district</placeName>, <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html">Vilna</placeName> region</p>
